<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="198" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                        <head>No. 198.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram<note n="*" xml:id="d198fn1">Shown
                                    to Mr. Bayard by Mr. Becerra, April 27.</note>.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>. [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1885-04-27">undated</date>].</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Becerra</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Colombian Minister, Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>Yesterday afternoon Aizpurú arranged with the American admiral that the
                            latter’s forces should retire to the railway station, those of Aizpurú
                            to maintain order in the city until the arrival of the expedition from
                            Cauca (Buenaventura), when they will go out of the city with full
                            liberty to give battle in the open country.</p>
                        <p>Between 7 and 8 at night the Americans retired.</p>
                        <closer><signed>TELL.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
